title: Bloor Homes Eastleigh Classic
text:
The Bloor Homes Eastleigh Classic was a women's professional <a href="golf">golf</a> tournament on the <a href="Ladies%20European%20Tour">Ladies European Tour</a>. It was first played in 1984 and held annually until 1991.
The tournament was played on the par–65 (34–31) <a href="Municipal%20Golf%20Course">municipal course</a> Fleming Park GC, Eastleigh, Hampshire, England, which closed permanently in 2008.
<a href="Jane%20Connachan">Jane Connachan</a> recorded a 58 in the first round and <a href="Dale%20Reid">Dale Reid</a> recorded a 58 in the final round of the 1991 tournament, <a href="Ladies%20European%20Tour%20records">Ladies European Tour records</a> as lowest rounds, as is Dale Reid's 1991 and <a href="Trish%20Johnson">Trish Johnson</a>'s 1990 72–hole raw score of 249.
